      <item>
        <title>Error: invalid CP949 character</title>
        <description>&lt;p&gt;In &lt;strong&gt;_layout.scss&lt;/strong&gt; file, &amp;lt; q &amp;gt; tag is used as a quotation mark. When apply this tag, it will display as “『』” on the page. One user report that on Windows it may cause a Error “invalid CPC949 character” when generate the site. A fast way to avoid this problem, please delete the lines of &amp;lt; q &amp;gt; tags in the &lt;strong&gt;_layout.scss&lt;/strong&gt; file.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;div class=&quot;highlighter-rouge&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;highlight&quot;&gt;&lt;pre class=&quot;highlight&quot;&gt;&lt;code&gt;### DELETE THE CODE BELOW IN _layout.scss FILE###
/**
 * New style for quotation.
 */
q:before {
content: '『';
color: #DD1144;
       font-weight:bold;
}
q:after {
content:'』';
color: #DD1144;
       font-weight:bold;
  }
&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
</description>
